1.name: Health State
1.description: Represents the current health of the entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is at a normal state of health.

2.name: Non-Critical
2.description: The entity is not at a normal state of health, but is still operational.

3.name: Critical
3.description: The entity is at a critical state of health. The entity may have suffered permanent damage, and may not be functional.

4.name: Fatal
4.description: The entity is at a fatal state of health.

5.name: Upper Non-Critical
5.description: The entity’s health is non-critical. The sensor is indicating that the entity is in the upper non-critical state.

6.name: Lower Non-Critical
6.description: The entity’s health is non-critical. The sensor is indicating that the entity is in the lower non-critical state.

7.name: Upper Critical
7.description: The entity’s health is critical. The sensor is indicating that the entity is in the upper critical state.

8.name: Lower Critical
8.description: The entity’s health is critical. The sensor is indicating that the entity is in the lower critical state.

9.name: Upper Fatal
9.description: The entity’s health is fatal. The sensor is indicating that the entity is in the upper fatal state.

10.name: Lower Fatal
10.description: The entity’s health is fatal. The sensor is indicating that the entity is in the lower fatal state.

2.name: Availability
2.description: The operational state of the entity.

1.name: Enabled
1.description: The entity is in an enabled state.

2.name: Disabled
2.description: The entity is in a disabled state.

3.name: Shutdown
3.description: The entity has been shut down.

4.name: Offline
4.description: The entity is in an offline test.

5.name: In Test
5.description: The entity is in a test mode.

6.name: Deferred
6.description: The entity has been deferred to function.

7.name: Quiescent
7.description: The entity is quiescent to function.

10.name: Failed
10.description: The entity is in a failed state.

12.name: Power Save Mode
12.description: The entity is in a power save mode.

15.name: Starting
15.description: The entity is starting or initializing.

3.name: Predictive Condition
3.description: The sense of whether the entity will experience an error condition in the future.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is not indicating a predictive error condition.

2.name: Predictive Failure
2.description: The entity is showing the characteristics of experiencing a failure in the future.

4.name: Redundancy Status
4.description: For a group of entities that together provide redundancy, represents the condition of the group.

1.name: Fully Redundant
1.description: All entities in the redundancy group are functioning correctly.

2.name: Redundancy Degraded
2.description: One or more entities in the redundancy group are unable to contribute to the redundancy. However, sufficient entities remain such that one or more additional entities would need to lose their ability to contribute for redundancy to be lost.

3.name: Redundancy Lost
3.description: No redundancy exists in the redundancy group. There may or may not be sufficient resources to continue with full operation using the remaining entities.

5.name: Health/Redundancy Trend
5.description: Represents whether the health (or redundancy) state has improved or is getting worse since the last value of health (or redundancy). For example, if Health State was Lower Non-Critical and is now Lower Critical, the trend is Degrading; if redundancy was Redundancy Lost and is now Redundancy Degraded, the trend is Improving.

1.name: Unchanged
1.description: The health/redundancy state of the entity is not changing.

2.name: Improving
2.description: The health/redundancy state of the entity has improved from the last health/redundancy state.

3.name: Degrading
3.description: The health/redundancy state of the entity has degraded from the last health/redundancy state.

6.name: Group Resource Level
6.description: Represents the resource level of the group of entities. Applies for a group of entities that provide redundancy as a group.

1.name: Sufficient Resources
1.description: The group has a sufficient number of entities to provide the level of service that the group is designed to provide.

2.name: Excess Resources
2.description: The group has more than the minimum number of entities to provide the level of service that the group is designed to provide.

3.name: Insufficient Resources
3.description: The group does not have a sufficient number of entities to provide the level of service that the group is designed to provide.

7.name: Redundancy Entity Role
7.description: Represents the role of the individual entity in a redundant group.

1.name: Is Hot Spare
1.description: This entity is reserved and on stand-by in the event of an error in a redundancy group. It is a passive member of a redundancy group.

2.name: In Redundancy Group
2.description: This entity is a member of a redundancy group. It may be active or passive.

3.description: In (non-redundant) Group The entity is a member of a group in which the service load is shared among the members of the group, but there is no fault-tolerant redundancy in the group.

8.name: Operational Status
8.description: The operational status of the entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is functioning with expected performance or capacity.

2.name: Degraded
2.description: The entity is functioning with reduced performance or capacity.

3.name: Completed
3.description: The entity has completed its function.

4.name: Migrating
4.description: The operation is being moved between entities.

5.name: Emigrating
5.description: The operation is being moved to a different entity.

6.name: Immigrating
6.description: The operation is being moved to this entity from a different entity.

9.name: Operational Stress Status
9.description: The stress status of the monitored entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is functioning with expected performance or capacity.

2.name: Stressed
2.description: The entity is functioning near the bounds of its acceptable performance or capacity.

10.name: Operational Fault Status
10.description: The fault status of the monitored entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No fault is present.

2.name: Error
2.description: A fault that causes an entity to deviate from its expected behavior is present.

3.name: Non-Recoverable Error
3.description: A fault that prohibits an entity from continuing to run is present.

11.name: Operational Running Status
11.description: The running status of the monitored entity.

1.name: Starting
1.description: The entity is beginning to run.

2.name: Stopping
2.description: The entity is ceasing to run.

3.name: Stopped
3.description: The entity is no longer running.

4.name: In Service
4.description: The entity is available for use.

5.name: Aborted
5.description: The entity has prematurely ended.

12.name: Operational Connection Status
12.description: Indicates whether the entity has the connectivity necessary to function.

1.name: Normal
1.description: Communication is established with the entity.

2.name: No Contact
2.description: Communication could not be established with the entity.

3.name: Lost Communication
3.description: The ability to communicate with the entity has stopped.

13.name: Presence
13.description: Indicates whether the entity is present in the system.

1.name: Present
1.description: The entity is successfully detected.

2.name: Not Present
2.description: The entity is not detected.

14.name: Performance
14.description: The performance of any type of entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is operating at a full functional level at full speed.

2.name: Throttled
2.description: The entity is operating at a full functional level at reduced speed.

3.name: Degraded
3.description: The entity is operating at a degraded functional level.

15.name: Configuration State
15.description: For any entity that can be dynamically configured and have a configuration state.

1.name: Valid Configuration
1.description: The entity is configured with valid configuration settings.

2.name: Invalid Configuration
2.description: The entity is configured with invalid configuration settings.

3.name: Not Configured
3.description: The entity is detected to not be configured.

4.name: Missing Configuration
4.description: The entity is missing its configuration settings.

16.name: Changed Configuration
16.description: For any entity that may have its configuration settings changed.

1.name: Normal
1.description: Configuration change is not detected.

2.name: Configuration Change Detected
2.description: A configuration change in the entity is detected.

17.name: Identify State
17.description: For entities that have an identify function, such as LEDs.

1.name: Identify State Unasserted
1.description: The entity’s identify function is not asserted.

2.name: Identify State Asserted
2.description: The entity’s identify function is asserted.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No version change is detected. If this is used by PLDM state set sensor, a manual re-arm would set this sensor back to the Normal state.

2.name: Version Change Detected – Compatible
2.description: A firmware or hardware version change of the entity is detected. No compatibility conflicts are detected.

3.name: Version Change Detected – Incompatible
3.description: A firmware or hardware version change of the entity is detected. The new version is incompatible with other entities.

19.name: Alarm State
19.description: The current activity of an alarm device.

1.name: Off
1.description: The alarm is not active.

2.name: Steady On
2.description: The alarm has been activated with the “steady on” setting.

3.name: Alternating On
3.description: The alarm has been activated with the “alternating on” setting.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The device is initialized.

2.description: Initialization in Progress The device is in the process of initializing.

3.name: Initialization Hung
3.description: The initialization process stopped responding.

4.name: Initialization Failed
4.description: The initialization process failed.

1.name: Normal A Thermal
1.description: Trip is not presently detected.

2.name: Thermal Trip
2.description: The entity automatically shut itself down due to an internal over-temperature condition.

1.description: Heartbeat present  Periodic messages or signal transitions that are used to verify the availability of communication with a particular node are detected.

2.description: Heartbeat lost Periodic messages or signal transitions that are used to verify the availability of communication with a particular node are not detected.

33.name: Link State
33.description: For any entity that has a data link to another entity.

1.name: Connected
1.description: The link is in the connected state.

2.name: Disconnected
2.description: The link is in the disconnected state.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The sensor is not detecting abnormal levels of smoke.

2.name: Smoke
2.description: The sensor detected abnormal levels of smoke.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The sensor is not detecting abnormal levels of humidity.

2.name: Humid
2.description: The sensor detected abnormal levels of humidity.

66.name: Door State
66.description: Indicates the state of the physical door.

1.name: Open
1.description: The sensor detects that the door is open.

2.name: Closed
2.description: The sensor detects that the door is closed.

67.name: Switch State
67.description: Indicates the state of an on/off switch. This could represent NMI, power switch, or any switch present on the system.

1.name: Pressed/On
1.description: The switch is in the on state.

2.name: Released/Off
2.description: The switch is in the off state.

96.name: Lock State
96.description: For an entity that can have a lock state.

1.name: Locked
1.description: The entity is in a locked state.

2.name: Unlocked
2.description: The entity is not in a locked state.

3.name: Locked Out
3.description: The entity is in a state in which the lock (physical or logical) cannot be unlocked in a normal manner. It is likely that elevated privileges are necessary to unlock the entity.

97.name: Physical Security
97.description: Security status related to physical hardware.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No abnormal physical security conditions are detected at this time.

2.name: Hardware Intrusion
2.description: A door, lock, or other mechanism protecting the internal system hardware from being accessed is detected as being in an insecure state.

3.name: Tampering
3.description: Physical tampering of the monitored entity is detected.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No unauthorized docking or undocking activity is detected.

2.name: Unauthorized Dock
2.description: The monitored entity is docked with a receiver in an unauthorized manner, or an unauthorized entity is docked with the monitored entity.

3.name: Unauthorized Undock
3.description: The monitored entity is undocked in an unauthorized manner, or an entity that was docked with the monitored entity is undocked in an unauthorized manner.

99.name: Hardware Security
99.description: States that should be associated with a "Security Hardware" type of entity, or a TPM.

1.name: Hardware Verified Security
1.description: Security hardware that is associated with maintaining security for the monitored entity is detected as being functional.

2.name: Hardware Unverified Security
2.description: Security hardware that is associated with maintaining security for the monitored entity failed one or more checks verifying that it is functional and complete.

100.name: Physical Communication Connection
100.description: Security status related to physical connection to an entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No physical connection issues are detected at this time.

2.name: Physical
2.description: Disconnect from Network A physical disconnection from the communication medium is detected. This may be due to the physical removal of the system.

101.name: Communication Leash Status
101.description: The status of the communication leash, which is the communications link between this entity and a remote network entity.

1.name: Leash Connected
1.description: Special periodic messages or transmissions that indicate physical connection to an expected network or communication medium are detected.

2.name: Leash Disconnected
2.description: Special periodic messages or transmissions that indicate physical connection to an expected network or communication medium are lost.

102.name: Foreign Network Detection Status
102.description: Status of a connection to an unexpected or unauthorized network or medium.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is not detected as being connected to an unrecognized or unauthorized network or communication medium.

2.name: Foreign Network Detected
2.description: The entity is connected to an unrecognized or unauthorized network or communication medium.

103.name: Password-Protected Access Security
103.description: Security status related to the access of the monitored entity.

1.name: Password Violations Detected No
1.description: No password violations are detected.

2.name: Password Violation Attempted
2.description: A password violation attempt is detected.

104.name: Security
104.description: Access – Privilege Level Indicates what privilege (if any) has been used for logging onto the entity.

1.name: Privilege Level Access Detected No
1.description: No privilege level is detected.

2.name: Read-only Privilege
2.description: The entity is a target of a logon using read-only privilege.

3.name: Full Control Privilege
3.description: The entity is a target of a logon using full control privilege.

1.name: Session Activated  A
1.description: PLDM session is activated with a PLDM terminus associated with the state sensor.

2.name: Session Deactivated A
2.description: PLDM session is deactivated with a PLDM terminus associated with the state sensor. PLDM State set

129.name: Software Termination Status
129.description: Status related to firmware of the operating system.

1.name: Normal
1.description: Software termination is not detected.

2.name: Termination Detected Software
2.description: Software termination is detected.

3.name: Critical
3.description: Stop during Load/Initialization The software entity failed during loading or initialization.

4.name: Run-time Critical Stop
4.description: The software entity incurred a run-time failure.

5.name: Graceful Shutdown Requested
5.description: The software entity has been requested to shut down gracefully.

6.name: Graceful Restart Requested
6.description: The software entity has been requested to restart gracefully.

7.name: Graceful Shutdown
7.description: The software entity has been shut down gracefully.

8.name: Termination Request Failed
8.description: The request to terminate the execution of the software entity failed.

160.name: Storage Media Activity
160.description: Represents the current activity of storage media that is part of a redundancy group.

1.name: Normal
1.description: The entity is not showing any array configuration or maintenance activity.

2.name: Parity
2.description: Check in Progress  A parity check is in progress on the storage entity.

3.name: Rebuilding/Remapping
3.description: A rebuild or remap operation is in progress on the storage entity.

4.name: Rebuild/Remap Aborted
4.description: A rebuild or remap operation has been aborted on the storage entity.

5.description: Prepare for Removal The storage entity has been prepared for removal.

192.name: Boot/Restart Cause
192.description: Represents the stimulus that booted the entity.

1.name: Powered Up
1.description: A start of the system is initiated by changing the entity’s state from powered off to powered on.

2.name: Hard Reset
2.description: A restart of the system is accomplished by activating the entity’s reset circuitry.

3.name: Warm Reset
3.description: A restart of the system is performed by software that does not involve powering the system off or activating the entity’s reset circuitry.

4.name: Manual Hard Reset
4.description: A restart is initiated by the user activation of a mechanical device (for example, pressing a button) and bypasses runtime software.

5.name: Manual Warm Reset
5.description: A restart is initiated by the user activation of a mechanical device (for example, pressing a button) and does not involve powering the entity off or activating the system’s reset circuitry.

6.name: System Restart
6.description: A restart of the entity is initiated by entity hardware components and accomplished by activating the system’s reset circuitry.

7.name: Watchdog Timeout
7.description: A restart of the entity is initiated in response to a detected system hang condition.

193.name: Boot/Restart Request
193.description: Indicates status of a request to restart the system in order to boot from a different source.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No boot/restart request is detected.

2.name: Boot/Restart Requested
2.description: A boot/restart request is detected.

194.name: Entity Boot Status
194.description: Indicates whether the entity was used as the boot device.

1.name: Normal
1.description: This entity was not used as a boot device.

2.name: Boot
2.description: Initiation from This Entity Was Detected This entity was used as a boot device.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No boot error is detected.

2.name: No Bootable Media
2.description: The device selected for the boot source could not be accessed, or the media in that device does not contain a boot sector.

3.name: Invalid Boot Sector
3.description: The boot sector does not contain valid data for booting.

4.description: Timeout for Boot Selection A timeout occurred while accessing the boot sector from the selected boot source (possible boot from default instead).

5.name: Remote Media Server Not Found
5.description: The server that provides the bootstrap program could not be located or a communication error occurred with the remote media server.

196.name: Boot Progress
196.description: System firmware or software booting status.

1.name: Boot Not Active
1.description: Boot-up of the firmware or software is not active. It may be already functional.

2.name: Boot Completed
2.description: The boot process of the firmware or software has completed.

3.name: Memory Initialization
3.description: The boot process is currently initializing the memory.

4.name: Hard-Disk Initialization
4.description: The boot process is currently initializing the hard disk.

5.name: Secondary Processor(s) Initialization
5.description: The boot process is currently initializing the secondary processors.

6.name: User Authentication
6.description: The boot process is processing the user authentication.

7.name: User-Initiated Setup System
7.description: System firmware or BIOS has entered the user system firmware or BIOS configuration setup.

8.name: USB Resource Configuration
8.description: System firmware or BIOS is currently configuring the USB resource.

9.name: PCI Resource Configuration
9.description: System firmware or BIOS is configuring the PCI resources.

10.name: Option ROM Initialization
10.description: The option ROM is being initialized.

11.name: Video Initialization
11.description: The video controller is being initialized.

12.name: Cache Initialization
12.description: The cache memory is being initialized.

13.name: SM Bus Initialization
13.description: The system firmware or BIOS is initializing the SM Bus.

14.name: Keyboard Controller Initialization
14.description: The system firmware or BIOS is initializing the keyboard controller.

15.name: Embedded Controller/Management Controller Initialization
15.description: The system firmware or BIOS is initializing the embedded management controller.

16.name: Docking Station Attachment
16.description: The main system unit is attaching to the docking station.

17.name: Enabling Docking Station
17.description: The system firmware or BIOS is enabling the docking station.

18.name: Docking Station Ejection
18.description: The main system unit is ejected from the docking station.

19.name: Disabling Docking Station
19.description: The system firmware or BIOS is disabling the docking station.

20.name: Calling Operating System Wake-Up Vector
20.description: The system firmware or BIOS is starting the operating system.

21.name: Starting Operating System Boot
21.description: Process (for example, calling INT 19h) The system firmware or BIOS is booting the operating system.

22.description: Baseboard or Motherboard Initialization The BIOS is initializing the motherboard.

23.name: Floppy Initialization The
23.description: BIOS is initializing the floppy drive.

25.name: Pointing Device Test The
25.description: BIOS is testing the pointing device.

26.name: Primary Processor Initialization The
26.description: BIOS is initializing the primary processor.

197.name: System Firmware Hang
197.description: Indicates if system firmware (BIOS) has been suspended.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No system firmware hang is detected.

2.name: System Firmware Hang Detected
2.description: The system firmware’s execution has suspended.

198.name: POST Errors
198.description: Errors detected in the system firmware (BIOS) power on self test.

1.name: No POST Error Detected
1.description: A system firmware error is not detected.

2.name: No System Memory Is Physically
2.description: Installed in the System. The system firmware determined that no system memory is physically installed in the system.

3.name: No Usable System Memory, All Installed Memory Has
3.description: Experienced an Unrecoverable Failure The system firmware determined that no usable system memory is available.

4.name: Unrecoverable Hard-Disk Device Failure
4.description: The system firmware detected that a hard-disk device has failed and is likely unusable for booting the operating system.

5.name: Unrecoverable System-Board Failure
5.description: The system firmware detected an unrecoverable error in the main system board or board set. This error may prevent the system from further operation.

6.name: Unrecoverable Diskette Subsystem Failure
6.description: The system firmware detected a failure in the diskette subsystem.

7.name: Unrecoverable Hard-Disk Controller Failure
7.description: The system firmware detected that a hard-disk controller has failed and is likely unusable for booting the operating system.

8.name: Unrecoverable
8.description: PS/2 or USB Keyboard Failure The system firmware detected a failure in the keyboard.

9.name: Removable Boot Media Not Found
9.description: The system firmware detected that a removable media device that was designated as a boot source does not have any media installed.

10.name: Unrecoverable Video Controller Failure
10.description: The system firmware detected a failure with a video controller. (The controller is likely unusable for driving the display device for a user interface for system firmware configuration.) This error is typically related to the display controller that drives a primary display device that would be used to locally display a user interface for system firmware configuration and as the primary local display used by the operating system.

11.name: No Video Device Detected
11.description: The system firmware has not been able to detect the presence of a video output device (computer display or computer monitor). This error is typically related to the primary display device that would be used to locally display a user interface for system firmware configuration and as the primary local display used by the operating system.

12.description: Firmware (BIOS) ROM Corruption Detected The system firmware detected that its own firmware image is corrupted.

13.name: CPU Voltage
13.description: Mismatch (processors that share same supply have mismatched voltage requirements) The system firmware detected that processors that share the same supply have mismatched voltage requirements, and is therefore preventing running further.

14.name: CPU Speed Matching Failure
14.description: The system firmware detected that the processors are operating with a combination of speeds that is not supported by the platform.

15.name: FRB1/BIST Failure
15.description: A processor BIST (built-in self test) failure is detected.

1.name: Normal
1.description: Logging is enabled. The log is not empty.

2.name: Reset/Cleared
2.description: Logging is enabled. A reset or clear signal has emptied the log.

3.name: Almost Full
3.description: Logging is enabled. The log has limited capacity for future entries.

4.name: Full
4.description: Logging is enabled. The log is full; no future entries can be added.

1.name: Unfiltered
1.description: Logging is enabled. All entries are logged.

2.name: Filtered
2.description: Logging is enabled, but some entries have been filtered.

1.name: Normal
1.description: A log timestamp change is not detected.

2.name: Timestamp Clock Sync
2.description: A log timestamp has been changed.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No interrupt is requested.

2.name: Requested  Interrupt
2.description: Interrupt is requested by entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No interrupt is received.

2.name: Received  Interrupt

1.name: Normal
1.description: No diagnostic interrupt is requested.

2.name: Interrupt Requested  Diagnostic
2.description: Diagnostic interrupt is requested by the entity. (This is equivalent to a front-panel NMI on some systems.)

1.name: Normal
1.description: No diagnostic interrupt is received.

2.name: Interrupt Received  Diagnostic
2.description: Diagnostic interrupt is received by the entity. (This is equivalent to a front-panel NMI on some systems.)

232.name: I/O Channel Check Requested I/O Channel Check NMI

1.name: Normal No I/O Channel Check
1.description: NMI is requested.

2.name: I/O Channel Check Requested  I/O Channel Check NMI
2.description: NMI is requested by the entity.

1.name: Normal No I/O Channel Check
1.description: NMI is received.

2.name: I/O Channel Check Received  I/O Channel Check NMI
2.description: NMI is received by the entity.

1.name: Normal No Fatal
1.description: NMI is requested.

2.name: Fatal Requested  Fatal NMI
2.description: NMI is requested by the entity.

1.name: Normal No Fatal
1.description: NMI is received.

2.name: Fatal Received Fatal NMI
2.description: NMI is received by the entity.

1.name: Normal No Software
1.description: NMI is requested.

2.name: Software Request  Software NMI
2.description: NMI is requested by the entity.

1.name: Normal No Software
1.description: NMI is received.

2.name: NMI Received Software
2.description: Software generated NMI is received by the entity.

1.name: Normal No
1.description: SMI is received.

2.name: SMI Received  System Management
2.description: Interrupt is received by the entity.

1.name: Normal No PCI Parity
1.description: Error is requested.

2.name: PCI PERR Requested PCI Parity
2.description: Error is requested by the entity.

1.name: Normal No PCI Parity
1.description: Error is received.

2.name: PCI PERR Received PCI Parity
2.description: Error is received by the entity.

1.name: Normal No PCI
1.description: SERR is requested.

2.name: PCI SERR Requested PCI System
2.description: Error is requested by the entity.

1.name: Normal No PCH
1.description: SERR is received.

2.name: PCI SERR Received  PCI System
2.description: Error is received by the entity.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No bus error is detected.

2.name: Correctable Error Bus
2.description: Bus transaction with correctable error occurred.

3.name: Uncorrectable Error Bus
3.description: Bus transaction with uncorrectable error occurred.

4.name: Fatal Error Bus
4.description: Bus transaction with fatal error occurred.

5.name: Degraded Bus
5.description: Bus is operating in a degraded state.

6.description: Bus timeout A bus transaction timeout occurred.

244.name: Watchdog Status
244.description: Conditions related to the watchdog timer.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No watchdog event is detected.

2.name: Timer Expired
2.description: The watchdog timer expired.

3.description: Pre-expire interrupt   Watchdog pre-timeout interrupt occurred.

256.name: Power Supply State
256.description: Conditions related to power units or power supplies.

1.name: Normal
1.description: No adverse conditions are detected with the power supply entity.

2.name: Power Input Lost
2.description: The power supply entity lost power from the source.

3.name: Power
3.description: Input out-of-range The power supplied to the power supply entity is out of range.

4.description: Power down/off  The power supply entity is in a power down state.

5.name: Power Cycle
5.description: The power supply entity is in a power cycle state.

6.name: Soft Power Control Failure
6.description: The power supply entity has encountered a soft power control failure.

7.name: Voltage
7.description: Input out of Range The power source voltage for the power supply entity is out of range.

8.name: Current
8.description: Input out of Range The power source current for the power supply entity is out of range.

9.name: Power Out Failed/Lost
9.description: The power output of the power supply entity is absent.

10.name: Thermal Trip
10.description: The power supply has experienced a thermal trip.

1.name: D0 The ACPI Device Power

296.name: Machine Check Error
296.description: Indicates presence of Machine Check Error (MCE).

1.name: MCE Not Detected A Machine Check
1.description: Error (MCE) is not detected.

2.name: MCE Detected A Machine Check
2.description: Error (MCE) occurred. This is a type of critical error that is detected by processor hardware that may be related to internal storage or state machine corruption or external errors that affect the ability of the hardware to continue processing the intended instruction flow. The error is typically associated with the generation of a corresponding software interrupt called a machine check exception. Depending on the error, it may or may not be able to be corrected by additional actions by software that handles the machine check exception.

297.name: Corrected Machine Check

1.name: Normal A Corrected Machine
1.description: Check (CMC) error is not detected.

2.name: Corrected MCE Detected   A Machine Check
2.description: Error has been detected and corrected. This is an error that is detected by processor hardware that may be related to internal storage or state machine corruption or external errors that would affect the ability of the hardware to continue processing the intended instruction flow, but that has been automatically corrected by the hardware.
